Arebia roughly consists of land in between the Red Sea and the Gulf of Oman. Ancient Arab peninsular consists of three parts 'Arebia petrea', 'Arebia Felix' and 'Arebia Dezerta'. Arebia petria (ruled from Petra) is in between Egypt and ancient Mesopotomia. Arebia felix (happy arebia) consists of modern Yemen and Arebia dezerta consists of modern South Arebia.

Prophet Muhammed is believed by Muslims to be the last prophet sent by God. Prophet Muhammed was born on 22nd April of 571 AD.   

